text:
I'll be real here, if a game has you genuinely terrified like this (1 hour in, idk what follows yet) I can't really be entertained. Like, sure sometimes it's funny when streamers are frightened by a jump scare or something but here it genuinely felt like it affected you on a deeper level. Idk if I am too overprotective or white-bread here but I don't want you to get borderline traumatized from a game.

On that note, a really nice horror game I can recommend is "I'm on observation duty". Idk if you have watched someone play it already but it is more of a puzzle game with horror elements. You are watching security cameras in a home and you have to notice if something is different in a room from how it should be. For example a chair has moved, there is a person in a room or there is writing on a door, to name a few. There are no jumpscares but it still is an extremely eerie game even I as a non-horror gamer can enjoy from time to time.
